      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "On Thursday and Friday, 40-60 cm of snow fell in the mountains, which was dry above about 1000 m and wetter at lower altitudes. The snowfall was accompanied by strong northerly winds, which blew the snow above the snow line to the old snow base or ground in many places.\n\nDuring the precipitation of more than a week ago, there was local fall of graupel, which is a potentially dangerous Weak layer. Locally, the layers of Graupel are 5-10 cm thick, possibly more.\nIn an old snow cover, the snow layers are well interconnected."
      },
